This paper deals with nonnegative matrix factorization, which is a popular technique in machine learning and data analysis. The paper discusses the non-uniqueness of NMF, which is a fundamental issue in the field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
